http://www.csathemovie.com/
 
 I went to see it last night. 
 
 It's an interesting movie. It's kinda funny, yet disturbing in spots.
 
 By the end of the movie, you see a few things differently.
 
 It gives you that "No way!" kinda feeling and you end up saying "Wow, I never thought about it that way before." or "I never looked at history that way or the current situation that way before either."
 
 Just go see it.

I definately want to see it (especially because it was put together by an instructor from KU.)
 
 But it needs to have an actual rating so it can open in more places.

Their website has a comments section. There are a lot of comments complaining about the lack of historical accuracy. Well, DUH! It's an alternate history. I think some people are just sensitive about anyone making the old South look bad.
